.TH CODEX_PLUGIN_MARKETPLACE 1 "July 2026" "codex-cli 0.142.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex\-plugin\-marketplace \- Add, list, upgrade, or remove configured plugin marketplaces
.SH SYNOPSIS
.EX
Usage: codex plugin marketplace [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add, list, upgrade, or remove configured plugin marketplaces
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B add
Add a local or Git marketplace to the configured marketplace sources
.TP
.B list
List plugin marketplaces Codex is currently considering and their roots
.TP
.B upgrade
Refresh configured Git marketplace snapshots
.TP
.B remove
Remove a configured marketplace source by name
.TP
.B help
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config <key=value>
Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`. Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.
.PP
Examples: \- `\-c model="o3"` \- `\-c 'sandbox_permissions=["disk\-full\-read\-access"]'` \- `\-c shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`
.TP
.B \-\-enable <FEATURE>
Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=true`
.TP
.B \-\-disable <FEATURE>
Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=false`
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help (see a summary with '\-h')
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR codex\-plugin (1),
.BR codex\-plugin\-marketplace\-add (1),
.BR codex\-plugin\-marketplace\-list (1),
.BR codex\-plugin\-marketplace\-upgrade (1),
.BR codex\-plugin\-marketplace\-remove (1)
